# Repository config globs

Repository globs from config should stack with globs supplied on the command
line, so both sources can surface repo-backed picker entries.

    :bins jj

> [!NOTE]
> 'jj' is available.

    :copy tests/fixtures/jjconfig.toml .jjconfig.toml (copied)

    :t rename-session -t 0 runner (success)
    :$ jj git init config-repo (exit: 0)
    :$ jj describe -R config-repo -m "config glob commit" (exit: 0)
    :$ jj git init cli-repo (exit: 0)
    :$ jj describe -R cli-repo -m "cli glob commit" (exit: 0)

    :w .config/sesh/sesh.toml (written)

```toml
[repo]
globs = ["config-repo"]
```

Launch `sesh` with an additional CLI glob, then verify each repository can be
selected from the same picker.

    :t new-session -d -s ui "sesh -r cli-repo" (success)
    :t resize-window -t ui:0 -x 120 -y 10 (success)
    :pane ui:0.0
    :settle (settled)

The config-supplied glob discovers `config-repo`.

    :k config
    :snap

```terminal
session: config
  1/4 | [C-r] repo: none
▌  config-repo                              ~/config-repo                                                              ┃
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
@  config glob commit
◆




```

The CLI-supplied glob discovers `cli-repo` in the same run.

    :k C-u cli
    :snap

```terminal
session: cli
  1/4 | [C-r] repo: none
▌  cli-repo                                 ~/cli-repo                                                                 ┃
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
@  cli glob commit
◆




```

